text:
Eleventh Avenue, east side,(buildings thereon, across the center) from W. 22nd (right) to 23rd (left) Streets, as viewed in an eastward direction on W. 22nd Street from Thirteenth Avenue. In the center, beyond the ramp of the West Side Express Highway appears a low peaked structure with an anchor decoration. This is occupied by the New York Port Society and bears No. 166-8 Eleventh Avenue. To the right of these views is the American Line pier and to the left an open park between 22nd and 23rd Streets.

May 15, 1931.
Views 1 and 2

P. L. Sperr

Eleventh Avenue, east side,(buildings thereon, across the center) from W. 22nd (right) to 23rd (left) Streets, as viewed in an eastward direction on W. 22nd Street from Thirteenth Avenue. In the center, beyond the ramp of the West Side Express Highway appears a low peaked structure with an anchor decoration. This is occupied by the New York Port Society and bears No. 166-8 Eleventh Avenue. To the right of these views is the American Line pier and to the left an open park between 22nd and 23rd Streets.

May 15, 1931.
Views 1 and 2

P. L. Sperr

Eleventh Avenue at 23rd Street seen from 22nd Street near Thirteenth Avenue across a small park. Because of the clear day, a very good view of the Empire State Building, Fifth Avenue at 34th Street, is given.

Summer, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.
